## ✅ MANDATORY CHECK BEFORE ANY SSH COMMAND

Before running ANY SSH command, you MUST verify:
1. The target IP matches `165.22.110.111` or `100.86.182.7`
2. The SSH key is `~/.ssh/id_ed25519_roo` (NOT `id_ed25519`)
3. If you see `104.248.225.250` anywhere in the command — **STOP**, it's the wrong VPS

## 🔐 SSH Command Template (CORRECT)

```bash
ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_roo root@165.22.110.111 "<command>"
# OR via Tailscale:
ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_roo root@100.86.182.7 "<command>"
```

## ❌ SSH Command Template (WRONG — DO NOT USE)

```bash
ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519 root@104.248.225.250 "<command>"
# This targets the SuperRoo VPS, NOT this project!
```
